23/04/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The leaders of the three parties of the so-called Democratic bloc in Serbia -- President Boris Tadic of the Democratic Party, Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica of the Serbian Democratic Party, and Mladjan Dinkic of G17 Plus -- met in secret on Thursday (April 19th), according to media reports Saturday.
The purpose of the meeting between potential coalition partners was twofold:
discuss the consequences of failing to reach an agreement on a new government, and rebuild mutual trust.
The 90-day deadline for forming the new government expires on May 14th.
(Politika, Blic, Glas Javnosti - 21/04/07;
B92 - 20/04/07)
